author: Donna Rachel Edmunds
title: Anti-Extremism Charity Staff Praised by May Made Antisemitic, Homophobic Comments
text: BIRMINGHAM, ENGLAND - JULY 06: People chat after prayers as the Birmingham Muslim community celebrate the festival of Eid in Small Heath Park on July 6, 2016 in Birmingham, England. Up to 70,000 people congregated in Small Heath Park to celebrate the Muslim holiday of Eid which marks the end of 30 days of dawn-to-sunset fasting during the holy month of Ramadan. (Photo by Christopher Furlong/Getty Images)
